  "2026-07-10T23:16:46.855Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: search rendering extraction remains in the broad docstring bundle; shared list/search timestamp predicates removed the final cross-command clone without changing filter semantics. pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint (0 clones), and focused search/list regression suites passed."
  "2026-07-11T00:02:35.336Z",codex-gpt5,"Scope boundary: this PR extracted search rendering and shared list/search timestamp filtering, reducing duplication to zero, but query-parsing and inline-field extraction remain outstanding and the acceptance target of <=1500 LOC per module is not yet met. Returning the item to open so only actively worked items remain in_progress."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T02:51:12.677Z",maintainer-agent,"Scope update after PR#506 (2026-07-11): the rendering slice is PARTIALLY done — search-rendering.ts extracted (137 lines) but search.ts is now 3740 physical / ~3330 effective lines (the static gate now counts only non-empty non-comment lines, changed in PR#506 to avoid penalizing docstrings — title's \"3119/3400\" numbers predate both changes). Effective count sits at ~98% of the 3400 cap, so this file is still one feature away from failing the gate. Remaining scope per PR#506 tracker note: query-parser + inline-field decomposition (keep the two parse layers' order from PR#290 intact). Suggested order: (1) inline field:value layer out first — it is the most self-contained and owns the list.ts:489 cross-file clone site; (2) query parser; (3) sweep remaining render helpers into search-rendering.ts."
  "2026-07-13T09:49:55.267Z",maintainer-agent,"Scope refresh 2026-07-13 (review pass #78): search.ts is now 3359 gate-normalized LOC (98.8% of the 3400 cap) — grown from the 3119 (92%) in this item's title. ~40 lines of headroom; any non-trivial search feature lands over the cap. Split urgency now on par with main.ts (see pm-yh8r census note of same date)."
